Left communism, or the communist left, is a political current that emerged in the 20th century, advocating for a more horizontal and democratic approach to socialism than the one presented by the Soviet Union.
Proponents of left communism have included Amadeo ...Maurice Thorez and the French Communist Party, who believed in a more Leninist approach to worker's control and class struggle within the capitalist system.
The historical origins of left communism come from a faction of the international communist movement that emerged in the late 19th and early 20th centuries, advocating for the direct overthrow of the bourgeois state and the establishment of a classless society through workers' soviets.
Left communism first came into focus as a response to the perceived failures of the Russian Revolution and the rise of Stalinism.
